     :math "sixth returns the element at position 5 (0-indexed)."
     :cs "Named accessor."))
  :row-3-dimension (
    (:setup "A named-position access for the sixth canonical slot."
     :rungs ((:domain "list" :code "(sixth week)")
             (:domain "sixth inning" :code "(inning-6 game)")
             (:domain "π_6 projection" :code "(define (pi6 t) (list-ref t 5))"))
     :explanation "In list, sixth names position 6. In baseball, sixth-inning is the sixth stanza. π_6 projects the sixth coordinate. All three share: named handle for position 6."
     :meta "The shape transfers where position 6 has stable meaning."))
